Block-Level Elements
 -they start on the a new linke
 -they expand from the left to right of that line
IE:
 <div>, <nav>, <article>, <address>, <footer>

Span Element= Inline Element
<span></span>
 -this element can be use to style a part of a 
 text, if use with CSS, it does not start on a 
 new line. It is an inLine Element 

 iframes 
 -used to load another website in the current webite.

 ie: 
 <iframe src="web url" height="" width="">
 </iframe>

 By using Name attribute, you can reference
 an ifram as a targe to display your site.
 <iframe>	Defines an inline frame
ie:
  <iframe src="demo_iframe.htm" name="iframe_a"></iframe>
   <p>
   <a href="https://www.w3schools.com" target="iframe_a">W3Schools.com</a>
   </p>
   ------------------JAVA SCRIPT------------
    JavaScript very often use the document.getElementById(id) method.

    internel usage
    <script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello JavaScript!";
</script>
   you can also make an external file and reference it in the head of your page

   -------------HTML Forms------------------------
<form></form>

   <form> 
   -form elements
   -forms element are input elements
   <input></input>
   -these input element allows user to inter acte with the form eighter by typing or clicking buttons.
   </forms>
   
   input close is a self-closing element

VALUE  TYPE  NAME

   to submit a form you must include a name for that form. else it won't be sent

   Value is a prefiller for a form element
   like how a submit button will have a value="submit now";
   <input type="submit" value="this is the text that will just be display on the button">

   Type is an attribute that define the over function of the element.
   <input type="text">
   <input type="radio">  
   -a circular button that allows you to pick from multiply chose type forms

to submit you need to give it an action file
<form action="/action_page.php">

ie:
   <form action="link to the file that will handle the form...usually php" target="where you want to load the result">

SELECT ELEMENT
 <select></select>
-this gives a drop down list
-the intems in that list will be the
 <options></option> element 

SELECT ELEMENT child Element
<select name="cars">
  <option value="volve"> Volvo </option>
</select>


SELECT ELEMENT size="" attribut

-to specify how much options you want to show
-use size="#ofelement you want to show" 
as an attribute
<select name="" size="3">
 <option value="volvo">Volvo</option>
  <option value="saab">Saab</option>
  <option value="fiat">Fiat</option>
  <option value="audi">Audi</option>
</select>


SELECT ELEMENT multiple="" attribut
this attribute allows user to pick multiple options

Form ELEMENT child Element
<textarea> 
</textarea>

-it give a space to write in
-name has to be assign

CREATING SPACE IN THE TEXT AREA
-rows=""   show how many lines you want
-cols=""   show how many character you want the person to be able to input when they type in the text area.
-Css width="" and height="" value can also be use 
to set the text input size and width for input.

